snippet.textDisplay: I believe that the illagers might have been allies of the builders. Why else would they want to build one. To obtain the knowledge and power of their former allies. Steve has that knowledge, he knows how to craft MOST of what the builders had. The builders and illagers both focus on magic. The illagers had totems of undying, and the builders had golden apples. In the video on the wither, it said that teamed mabey the builders teamed up with the witches to develope a way to build dead bodies back to life, who are allies of the illagers due to their presence in raids. This means that the builders probably allied with illagers too. All three had magic, all three were allies. And so the quest began, they found ways to escape death and build life ( snow and iron golems, curing zombie villagers, experiments with soul sand and blue wool, golden apples, potions, enchantments, lapis, and totems). And then the builders fell... but the illagers and witches kept going... they were obsessed with power and also wanted to bring the builders back so they could continue their work. They wanted to go to the end... perhaps to recover the lost builders. So they tried using wool and exidentaly created zombies. To cure them, they uncovered the long lost recipe for golden apples (this claim is supported by the igloo basements). Then... it worked... they made Steve! But he was defiant and was only concerned about getting tp the end... he didn't want to help them. The illagers were FURIOUS. This is why they hate Steve so much. Steve was a traitor. He went against the allience... the alliance that had stood for SOOOOO long. This is why witches and illagers are hostile to him. He betrayed them:(
snippet.textOriginal: I believe that the illagers might have been allies of the builders. Why else would they want to build one. To obtain the knowledge and power of their former allies. Steve has that knowledge, he knows how to craft MOST of what the builders had. The builders and illagers both focus on magic. The illagers had totems of undying, and the builders had golden apples. In the video on the wither, it said that teamed mabey the builders teamed up with the witches to develope a way to build dead bodies back to life, who are allies of the illagers due to their presence in raids. This means that the builders probably allied with illagers too. All three had magic, all three were allies. And so the quest began, they found ways to escape death and build life ( snow and iron golems, curing zombie villagers, experiments with soul sand and blue wool, golden apples, potions, enchantments, lapis, and totems). And then the builders fell... but the illagers and witches kept going... they were obsessed with power and also wanted to bring the builders back so they could continue their work. They wanted to go to the end... perhaps to recover the lost builders. So they tried using wool and exidentaly created zombies. To cure them, they uncovered the long lost recipe for golden apples (this claim is supported by the igloo basements). Then... it worked... they made Steve! But he was defiant and was only concerned about getting tp the end... he didn't want to help them. The illagers were FURIOUS. This is why they hate Steve so much. Steve was a traitor. He went against the allience... the alliance that had stood for SOOOOO long. This is why witches and illagers are hostile to him. He betrayed them:(

snippet.textDisplay: Wouldn’t the Zombies have to have been based on the ancient race of builders, because the player doesn’t exist in-universe until the world is generated, after the zombies have been created? This implies that Steve/Alex might be descendants of that race. Also, if the player plays as Alex (or another skin), then the blue wool wouldn’t apply to their coloring, like how Alex has a light green shirt and grey pants, not blue. This also points to Zombies being based off of that ancient race. Thank you for coming to my Ted-talk.
